{"tag":"section","attrib":{"id":"ida9df4af1-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s2826"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"2826"},"text":"§ 2826.","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Military family housing: local comparability of room patterns and floor areas","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"ida9df4af2-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s2826/a"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"a"},"text":"(a)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" ","children":[{"tag":"inline","attrib":{},"text":"Local Comparability","children":[],"tail":".—"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":"In the construction, acquisition, and improvement of military family housing, the Secretary concerned shall ensure that the room patterns and floor areas of military family housing in a particular locality (as designated by the Secretary concerned for purposes of this section) are similar to room patterns and floor areas of similar housing in the private sector in that locality.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"ida9df4af3-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s2826/b"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"b"},"text":"(b)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" ","children":[{"tag":"inline","attrib":{},"text":"Requests for Authority for Military Family Housing","children":[],"tail":".—"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"ida9df4af4-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s2826/b/1"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"1"},"text":"(1)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" In submitting to Congress a request for authority to carry out the construction, acquisition, or improvement of military family housing, the Secretary concerned shall include in the request information on the net floor area of each unit of military family housing to be constructed, acquired, or improved under the authority.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"ida9df4af5-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s2826/b/2"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"2"},"text":"(2)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" In this subsection, the term “net floor area”, in the case of a military family housing unit, means the total number of square feet of the floor space inside the exterior walls of the unit, excluding the floor area of an unfinished basement, an unfinished attic, a utility space, a garage, a carport, an open or insect-screened porch, a stairwell, and any space used for a solar-energy system.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"sourceCredit","attrib":{"id":"ida9df4af6-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5"},"text":"(Added ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/97/214/s2/a"},"text":"Pub. L. 97–214, § 2(a)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1982-07-12"},"text":"July 12, 1982","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/96/159"},"text":"96 Stat. 159","children":[],"tail":"; amended "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/100/26/s7/k/3"},"text":"Pub. L. 100–26, § 7(k)(3)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1987-04-21"},"text":"Apr. 21, 1987","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/101/284"},"text":"101 Stat. 284","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/102/190/dB/tXXVIII/s2808"},"text":"Pub. L. 102–190, div. B, title XXVIII, § 2808","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1991-12-05"},"text":"Dec. 5, 1991","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/105/1540"},"text":"105 Stat. 1540","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/104/106/dB/tXXVIII"},"text":"Pub. L. 104–106, div. B, title XXVIII","children":[],"tail":", §§ 2814, 2815, "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1996-02-10"},"text":"Feb. 10, 1996","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/110/553"},"text":"110 Stat. 553","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/104/201/dA/tX/s1074/a/17"},"text":"Pub. L. 104–201, div. A, title X, § 1074(a)(17)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1996-09-23"},"text":"Sept. 23, 1996","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/110/2659"},"text":"110 Stat. 2659","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/106/398/s1/dB/tXXVIII/s2803/a/1"},"text":"Pub. L. 106–398, § 1 [div. B, title XXVIII, § 2803(a)(1)]","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2000-10-30"},"text":"Oct. 30, 2000","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/114/1654"},"text":"114 Stat. 1654","children":[],"tail":", 1654A–413.)"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"notes","attrib":{"type":"uscNote","id":"ida9df4af7-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"editorialNotes","id":"ida9df4af8-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Editorial Notes","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"amendments","id":"ida9df4af9-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Amendments","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"2000—","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/106/398"},"text":"Pub. L. 106–398","children":[],"tail":" amended section catchline and text generally. Prior to amendment, section consisted of subsecs. (a) to (i) which limited the net floor area allowed in the construction, acquisition, and improvement of military family housing units."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1996—Subsec. (e). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/104/106/s2814"},"text":"Pub. L. 104–106, § 2814","children":[],"tail":", struck out at end “The authority provided by this subsection shall expire on "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1994-09-30"},"text":"September 30, 1994","children":[],"tail":".”"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsec. (i). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/104/106/s2815"},"text":"Pub. L. 104–106, § 2815","children":[],"tail":", added subsec. (i)."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsec. (i)(1). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/104/201"},"text":"Pub. L. 104–201","children":[],"tail":" substituted “"},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1996-02-10"},"text":"February 10, 1996","children":[],"tail":"” for “the date of the enactment of the National Defense Authorization Act for Fiscal Year 1996”."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1991—Subsecs. (d) to (h). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/102/190"},"text":"Pub. L. 102–190","children":[],"tail":" added subsecs. (d) and (e) and redesignated former subsecs. (d) to (f) as (f) to (h), respectively."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1987—Subsec. (f). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/100/26"},"text":"Pub. L. 100–26","children":[],"tail":" inserted “the term” after “In this section,”."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"statutoryNotes","id":"ida9df4afa-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Statutory Notes and Related Subsidiaries","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"effectiveDateOfAmendment","id":"ida9df4afb-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Effective Date of 2000 Amendment","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/106/398/s1/dB/tXXVIII/s2803/b"},"text":"Pub. L. 106–398, § 1 [div. B, title XXVIII, § 2803(b)]","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2000-10-30"},"text":"Oct. 30, 2000","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/114/1654"},"text":"114 Stat. 1654","children":[],"tail":", 1654A–413, provided that:"},{"tag":"quotedContent","attrib":{"origin":"/us/pl/106/398/s1/dB/tXXVIII/s2803/b"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"1"},"text":"“(1)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" The amendments made by subsection (a) [amending this section] shall take effect on ","children":[{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2001-10-01"},"text":"October 1, 2001","children":[],"tail":", but the Secretary of Defense shall anticipate the requirements of "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t10/s2826"},"text":"section 2826 of title 10","children":[],"tail":", United States Code, as added by such subsection, when preparing the budget request for new construction, acquisition, or improvement of military family housing for fiscal year 2002."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"2"},"text":"“(2)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t10/s2826"},"text":"Section 2826 of title 10","children":[],"tail":", United States Code, as in effect on "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2001-09-30"},"text":"September 30, 2001","children":[],"tail":", shall continue to apply with respect to the construction, acquisition, or improvement of military family housing commenced on or before that date.”"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"effectiveDate","id":"ida9df4afc-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Effective Date","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"For effective date and applicability of section, see ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/97/214/s12/a"},"text":"section 12(a) of Pub. L. 97–214","children":[],"tail":", set out as a note under "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t10/s2801"},"text":"section 2801 of this title","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":null}
